It’s hard to put the past 8 months into words after years of building a dream career. The thing about dreams is that they can grow and develop into bigger and better things than someone can ever imagine. I’m happy to share my start as Director Social Media Strategy at @octagon. I’m beyond excited to be leading social for a world-class roster of athletes and talent across, traditional, Olympic, and action sports. Here’s to bigger and better, and to my new home!
🏆💕

Happy to be here. 🧡 @octagon

Back on the sunshine grind. 🎾🌴 @octagon

I always had a picture in my mind but it was fuzzy. A rad shape, good grass and a walk to the beach. Five years ago Alex and I moved to California with career goals. The path wasn’t exactly what we imagined, sometimes it was even better and sometimes worse. If you had told younger us and our U-Haul that we’d someday return to a beach house, Alex working for @disney and me one of the top sports agencies in the world, I probably would have said LFG, but in a bit of disbelief. My favorite part of our journey is our growth, and how unexpected turns pushed us into this moment. I’m convinced that willing things into existence and working for what you want is a thing. Still waiting for someone to pinch me because this new chapter is a dream come true. Now taking reservations for summer 2023. 🔑🏠🌴💜🌈🏄🏼‍♀️🐚🌅💕🌊✨ @soot_design

A full circle moment. Honored to be the keynote speaker for Flagler College Design Week to share my journey on Rethinking Resilience. 🌈✨

A year after graduating I started to realize resilience wasn’t what I thought it was, that doing everything in my power wasn’t always enough. Fast forward to present day and I’m still learning what it means to be resilient even in challenging times. 

Rethinking Resilience unpacks each career milestone, providing takeaways and expectations learned along the way. My journey showcases the relationship between resilience, goals, and expectations bringing to light what it actually takes to chase dreams. 

Thank you @flaglercollege @flaglercollegeart @aigaflaglerstudentgroup

New episode out with @elise_crigar about turning setbacks into fuel 🎙️

Join @emilieuttrup and Elise Crigar in this engaging episode of Resurface as they dive deep into the world of shaping a career in the sports industry. Elise, a professional who has worked with renowned brands such as Hurley and WSL, now holds a director role at Octagon, where she works closely with some of the most successful athletes in the world.

In this episode, Emilie and Elise discuss the importance of hard work, self-investment, trust in your vision, and never giving up. Elise shares her professional journey, including how she bounced back after losing her dream job, highlighting the determination and resilience needed for success.

Tune in for an episode that leaves you inspired and motivated to follow your own goals and dreams (link in bio) 💫

#podcast #career #goalsetting
